messages.content:
The `checkInterfaceConflictProperties` method in the `TypeCheck` class is responsible for checking interface conflict properties. It iterates over the current property names of an interface and compares the property types with the properties of the interface being extended. If there is an incompatible property type, it reports an error.

Based on this code snippet, the NullPointerException at line 1574 could occur if `implicitProto` is null, leading to a NullPointerException when trying to invoke `getOwnPropertyNames()` on a null object.

To address this issue, the code may need to include a null check for `implicitProto` before calling `getOwnPropertyNames()`. This check will ensure that the method is not called on a null object, thereby preventing the NullPointerException.

The methods that need to be fixed in the `TypeCheck` class are:
- `checkInterfaceConflictProperties(com.google.javascript.jscomp.NodeTraversal, com.google.javascript.rhino.Node, java.lang.String, java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String, com.google.javascript.rhino.jstype.ObjectType>, java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String, com.google.javascript.rhino.jstype.ObjectType>, com.google.javascript.rhino.jstype.ObjectType)`
